com.interpss.dc

Interface DcBus

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Bus, com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ExtensionElement, NameTag, NetworkedElement, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    PVDcBus
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DcBusImpl, PVDcBusImpl

    public interface DcBus
extends Bus
    A representation of the model object 'Dc Bus'.

    The following features are supported:

    • Code
    • Voltage
    • Source Power
    • Load
    See Also:
    DcSystemPackage.getDcBus()

        double getVoltage()
        Returns the value of the 'Voltage' attribute.

        If the meaning of the 'Voltage' attribute isn't clear, there really should be more of a description here...

        dc bus voltage in pu. Voltage of voltage source keeps constant, while voltage of load bus is updated during the Loadflow run.
